{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/blog/2024-07-17-how-to-add-left-and-right-border-in-react-js/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"excerpt":"Hi Friends üëã, Welcome To aHoisting! To add left and right border in react js, you can set  and  in . It will add left and right border in react js. Today, I am‚Ä¶","html":"<p>Hi Friends üëã,</p>\n<p>Welcome To aHoisting!</p>\n<p>To add left and right border in react js, you can set <code class=\"language-text\">border-right-style: solid;</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">border-left-style: solid;</code> in <code class=\"language-text\">.border-left-right</code>. It will add left and right border in react js.</p>\n<p>Today, I am going to show you, how to add left and right border in react js.</p>\n<p>Table of contents</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Install and create a new React app.</li>\n<li>Import react component.</li>\n<li>Create a Component.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Let‚Äôs start with the first step.</p>\n<h3>Step 1: Install and create a new React app.</h3>\n<p>First you have to install the React project. You should use <code class=\"language-text\">create-react-app</code> command to create a new React project.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">npx create<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>react<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\ncd my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\nnpm start</code></pre></div>\n<h3>Step 2: Import react component.</h3>\n<p>After installing, you have to import your React component. To do this, add the following line to the top of your component file.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"./App.css\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<h3>Step 3: Create a Component.</h3>\n<p>You can use <code class=\"language-text\">className=\"border-left-right\"</code> to add left and right border in react js.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>div className<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"border-left-right\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  This div has left and right borders<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>\n<h3>Add left and right border example.</h3>\n<p>The below code is an example of a React. You have to import <code class=\"language-text\">\"./App.css\"</code> and set <code class=\"language-text\">border-right-style: solid;</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">border-left-style: solid;</code> in <code class=\"language-text\">.border-left-right</code> to add left and right border in react js.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">App.js</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"./App.css\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">App</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>div className<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"border-left-right\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      This div has left and right borders<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n <span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> App<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">App.css</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token selector\">.border-left-right</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">border-right-style</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> solid<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">border-left-style</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> solid<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">width</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> max-content<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">padding</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 10px<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>In the above code example, I have used the <code class=\"language-text\">border-right-style: solid;</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">border-left-style: solid;</code> to add left and right border in react js.</p>\n<p>Check the output of the above code.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 421px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/319589c1ff46240540e82bff96b244d1/ced8d/left-and-right-border.webp\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 89.24050632911393%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/webp;base64,UklGRlwAAABXRUJQVlA4IFAAAACwAwCdASoUABIAPtFYpk0oJSOiMBgIAQAaCWUAAC5uXcBW5RuIAADLT5I0tKx+L/Fb1Y2HSELTmo6CT1xrm9jp/wuZbB2iGtKC/2FfAAAAAA=='); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"React, add, left, and, right, border\"\n        title=\"React, add, left, and, right, border\"\n        src=\"/static/319589c1ff46240540e82bff96b244d1/ced8d/left-and-right-border.webp\"\n        srcset=\"/static/319589c1ff46240540e82bff96b244d1/81b7c/left-and-right-border.webp 158w,\n/static/319589c1ff46240540e82bff96b244d1/6ea66/left-and-right-border.webp 315w,\n/static/319589c1ff46240540e82bff96b244d1/ced8d/left-and-right-border.webp 421w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 421px) 100vw, 421px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>All the best üëç</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"How to add left and right border in react js?","tags":["React"],"date":"July 17, 2024","description":"Example of add left and right border in react js with step by step tutorial - aHoisting","social_image":{"absolutePath":"/Users/mac/Documents/hoisting/ahoisting/static/media/template/reactjs.jpg"}}},"prev":{"frontmatter":{"title":"How to add left and right padding in react js?"},"fields":{"slug":"/blog/2024-07-18-how-to-add-left-and-right-padding-in-react-js/"}},"next":{"frontmatter":{"title"